# 15. 本気で言ってんのか

Akito: You won't perform anymore? What are you talking about?
Akito: You know you aren't any good with jokes, so stop messing around.
Toya: This isn't a joke.
Akito: What's wrong? Did your old man say something again?
Toya: .....
Toya: This is my own decision. Our kind of music doesn't mean anything. It's just a bunch of kids making some noise.
Akito: Are you being serious right now?
Toya: You're the one who said I wasn't any good at making jokes.
Akito: That's going too far.
Akito: Our music has no meaning? Try saying that again! I won't take this, not even from you, Toya!
Akito: What are you gonna do if you quit, anyway? Go crawling back and let your dad control you again after saying how much you hated things? How is that any more meaningful?!
Toya: ...Let go of me.
Akito: Get back here! This conversation isn't over, Toya!
Akito: !!
Toya: Don't you think it's about time you grew up and stopped chasing after some tiny event that no-one's even heard of outside of this town?
Akito: Why, you!
Toya: !!
Akito: Fine then, leave!
Akito: And never show your face around here again!
Toya: .....
Kohane & An: Hello!
MEIKO: Hi there, you two! It's nice to see you. Oh? You cut your hair.
Len: Kohane, why'd you change your hair?
An: Hehe. It's proof of her resolve, right Kohane?
Kohane: That's right!
Miku: So, how did it go?
Kohane: Thanks to An and everyone's support, I managed to perform again. And it went great! Thank you so much for your help!
Miku: That's great.
Kohane: Miku, why are you guys taking such an interest in us?
Miku: That's because we want all of you to discover your true feelings.
Miku: When that happens, they'll be transformed into a new song. Our wish is that such feelings will give birth to all kinds of new songs.
Kohane: Our feelings will change into a song...
Len: Yeah! That's why we've gotta make those other two who haven't been here yet realize their true feelings as well!
An: Oh, that's right. You mentioned this place was made from the feelings of four people. Do you know who the other two are?
Len: We haven't had a chance to talk to them yet, but I'm sure Akito and Toya will come visit soon!
An: Akito and Toya?!
Len: Wh-What? Are they friends of yours?
An: W-Well, I wouldn't exactly call them friends... It's... complicated.
An: I guess they did both say they dreamt of surpassing RAD WEEKEND, but...
Miku: Hopefully, they'll visit us soon.
Akito: .....
Akito: Hey, you've been singing around here a lot lately.
Toya: What if I have?
Akito: Nothing, I just noticed, that's all. I was curious why you'd choose to sing here, of all places.
Toya: ...It's nothing worth getting curious about.
Akito: Your rhythm and pitch are always so precise. I bet you've been into music a while.
Toya: ...I guess you could say that.
Akito: Oh? Some kind of story behind it, I take it?
Toya: ...Nothing important. It's just...
Toya: I feel like I can be myself when I'm singing like this.
Akito: So you've got music to thank for keeping you going, then?
Akito: Now I'm really interested. Hey, how would you like to try singing together?
An's Father: So you two decided to team up, huh?
Akito: Yeah. There's one more thing we wanted to talk to you about. Care to have a guess?
Toya: We've decided to call ourselves BAD DOGS.
Akito: What the heck, Toya?! I wanted to tell him!
Toya: Then just say it. No reason to act so smug and drag it out.
Akito: How is it that someone who talks as little as you always cuts in right at the worst time?
Akito: ...Tsk
Kohane: Hello! Oh, Sh-Shinonome...
Akito: What?
Kohane: Eep! N-Nothing!
Kohane: S-So scary... Shinonome seems upset. Did something happen?
An: I'm not sure. I was planning on telling him about the SEKAI, but he's been acting like that ever since he got here.
Kohane: Huh? Aoyagi isn't here today?
An: No, I haven't seen him. I wonder if they had a fight or something.
Kohane: A fight?
An: It'll probably blow over soon. Oh, hey. One of the guys from a club nearby called SPACE asked me if we'd like to perform. What do you think? Want to do it?
Kohane: Y-Yeah. I'd like to try.
Akito: .....
Kohane: (I wonder if Shinonome and Aoyagi are all right.)
